Here is a detailed feature-comparison of Webform and Contact Storage 8.x-1.x. It's worth noting that Contact Storage relies on the Contact module which in turn relies on the Field UI; Contact Storage out of the box is a minimalistic solution with limited (but useful!) functionality. This means it can be extended with core mechanisms such as CRUD entity hooks and overriding services; also there's a greater chance that a general purpose module will play nicely with it (eg. the Conditional Fields module is for entity form displays in general, not the Contact module).
